/**
 * Feature: Web Application Firewall (WAF)
 *
 * TODO: Implement basic web application firewall
 *
 * MISSING CAPABILITIES (vs Wordfence):
 * - Request filtering and blocking
 * - IP address blocking (individual, range, country)
 * - Rate limiting (all endpoints, not just login)
 * - Attack pattern detection (SQL injection, XSS, etc.)
 * - Threat intelligence integration
 * - Whitelist/blacklist management
 * - Automatic IP blocking for repeated violations
 * - WAF rules engine
 * - Traffic analytics
 * - Geolocation-based blocking
 *
 * IMPLEMENTATION NOTES:
 * - Hook early (muplugins_loaded or earlier)
 * - Store blocked IPs in database for fast lookup
 * - Use transients for rate limiting counters
 * - Add settings page for WAF configuration
 * - Log all blocked requests
 * - Support CIDR notation for IP ranges
 *
 * ATTACK PATTERNS TO DETECT:
 * - SQL injection attempts
 * - XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
 * - Directory traversal (../)
 * - File inclusion attacks
 * - Command injection
 * - Suspicious user agents
 * - Known malicious IPs
 *
 * BLOCKING METHODS:
 * - IP address (exact match)
 * - IP range (CIDR)
 * - Country (GeoIP)
 * - User agent pattern
 * - Referrer pattern
 * - Rate limiting (requests per minute)
 *
 * INTEGRATION POINTS:
 * - Extend existing brute force protection
 * - Integrate with activity logger
 * - Add to security dashboard
 * - Provide WP-CLI commands
 *
 * PERFORMANCE CONSIDERATIONS:
 * - Cache blocked IP list in memory
 * - Use fast lookups (hash tables)
 * - Minimal processing overhead
 * - Exit early for blocked requests
 *
 * @package WPS\CoreSupport
 * @since 1.2601.75000
 */

